It's not a joke! President Jacob Zuma has joined social media. "I have decided to move with times and join various social media platforms such as Twitter, Facebook and Instagram." These were the words of former president Jacob Zuma when he announced in a video clip that he has joined social media. The former president's first tweet is of a video of himself, in which he makes the announcement. He said: "Hello, everyone. I have decided to move with times to join this important area of conversation because I hear that many people are talking about me."I felt it is necessary that I should join in and be part of the conversation."It's me, the former president, Jacob Zuma."Zuma's handle on witter, Instagram and Facebook @PresJGZuma. EFF president Julius Malema welcomed with on Twitter saying: "Welcome baba". 